					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-103504#post-2299230</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-103504/lowest-rated-pages#post-2299230</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2015 14:08:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Thekillerax</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1832151</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm relatively sure everyone who's written for this site has been on this page at least once. It's no big deal. It's not like this page is a compilation of the worst articles of all time, since negatively rated articles are deleted on a regular basis, so being on this list just means your article didn't reach the positives, which is something that has happened to more or less everybody. Just pick yourself up and carry on. I'd recommend setting up a sandbox and running stored drafts through the forums and chat before posting so you can receive critique.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
